title: DCQN-Matrix-Axiomatik-LLM-Protocol for zero hallucination and reproducible LLM reasoning
abstract: >-
  The DCQN-Matrix-Axiomatik-LLM-Protocol is a deterministic evaluation framework
  for large language models. It integrates the DCQN structural model, real-text
  verification, and DOI-anchored audit chains to enforce zero hallucination,
  strict reproducibility, and machine-logic boundary conditions in LLM
  reasoning.
